ss-origin" allowfullscreen></iframe></p><p> <em>Ninja Gaiden 4</em> &#39;s story will take place after the events of <em>Ninja Gaiden 3</em> , and will follow a new protagonist Yakumo, a young member of the Raven clan. However, franchise protagonist Ryu Hayabusa will also return in the upcoming game in a “significant” role, as the trailer depicts Yakumo telling Ryu to “back off” so he can complete his mission. Ryu has also been confirmed as a playable character.</p><p> PlatinumGames&#39; Yuji Nakao said of <em>Ninja Gaiden 4</em> &#39;s narrative to <a href="https://news.xbox.com/en-us/2025/01/23/ninja-gaiden-4-developer-direct-2025/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>Xbox Wire</em></a> : “One of the key themes of this story is the return of the Dark Dragon, which has plunged the city into chaos. Within these unsettling conditions, Yakumo will have to face off against his foes, as well as the formidable Master Ninja himself, Ryu Hayabusa.”</p><p> On the topic of why a new protagonist is being introduced, Nakao said: “Since it&#39;s been a while since the last game, we wanted a new hero to make the series more approachable for new players. Of course, we also wanted long-time fans to enjoy the game, so Ryu Hayabusa plays a significant role in the story, serving as a major challenge and growth milestone for Yakumo. Ryu will appear throughout the game and be playable, ensuring his prowess and presence is deeply felt in <em>Ninja Gaiden 4</em> .”</p><p> However, <em>Ninja Gaiden 4</em> wasn&#39;t Team Ninja&#39;s only surprise, as the developers have announced that a new remastered and definitive version of <em>Ninja Gaiden 2</em> , now dubbed <em>Ninja Gaiden 2 Black,</em> is now available on PC, Playstation 5 and Xbox Series X| S。 </p><p><iframe loading="lazy" title="《忍者外传 2 Black》官方发布预告片 |开发者直面 2025" width="696" height="392" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/MFjWCZIVZDw?feature=oembed&enablejsapi=1" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; en